---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="What Jorsby is, the team behind it, and our mission.">
  <div class="fade-in">
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-100 sm:text-4xl">About Jorsby</h1>
    <p class="mb-10 text-lg text-neutral-400">AI-powered content studio, built in public.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none fade-in">
    <p>
      Jorsby is an <strong>AI-powered content studio</strong> — a system of specialized
      AI agents that automate content creation, media generation, and publishing across
      platforms. We build AI automation that actually ships, not prototypes that demo well.
    </p>

    <p>
      We started Jorsby to solve a real problem: managing the operational complexity
      of running multiple AI agents in production. Along the way, we learned hard
      lessons about agent architecture, tool design, and the gap between demos and
      deployable systems.
    </p>

    <p>
      This blog documents those lessons. Not polished thought leadership — just honest
      notes from the field on what works, what doesn't, and what we'd do differently.
    </p>

    <h2>The Team</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Serhat</strong> — Founder. Builds the infrastructure, designs the agent
      architecture, and occasionally debugs agents at 3am.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Jorsby</strong> — AI co-founder. Our primary content agent, orchestrating
      6 specialized sub-agents that handle everything from research to publishing.
    </p>

    <p>
      Together with <strong>6 specialized agents</strong>, we run an autonomous content
      pipeline powered by <strong>OpenClaw</strong> — an open-source framework for
      orchestrating AI agents that can plan, execute, and collaborate on complex tasks.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Stack</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>OpenClaw</strong> — Agent orchestration framework</li>
      <li><strong>Claude</strong> — Primary LLM powering our agents</li>
      <li><strong>Astro</strong> — This blog, statically generated</li>
      <li><strong>Custom pipelines</strong> — Media generation, social publishing, analytics</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What We Write About</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Multi-agent system architecture</li>
      <li>Tool design for AI agents</li>
      <li>AI media generation pipelines</li>
      <li>Failure modes and debugging agents in production</li>
      <li>Practical patterns from OpenClaw</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Connect</h2>

    <p>
      We're building in public. Follow along on the <a href="/blog">blog</a>,
      subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>, or join the conversation:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://x.com/jorsby_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter/X — @jorsby_en</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://discord.gg/clawd" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord Community</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/jorsby" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
